⚙️ SAME SAME, BETTER — Universal Repass Template

🧩 Step 1 — Identify the Invariant Core

Ask:
	•	What would break this if removed?
	•	What makes it recognizably itself?

Output (write it):
	•	Core function:
	•	Core identity:
	•	Core feel:

⸻

🔍 Step 2 — Strip to Minimum Viable Form

Force reduction:
	•	Remove anything non-essential
	•	Collapse multiple ideas → 1 idea

Rule:

If it doesn’t strengthen the core, cut it.

⸻

🧱 Step 3 — Define the Constraint Profile

Pick 3–5 rules max:

Examples:
	•	max 2 concepts
	•	simple over complex
	•	readable in 1 glance
	•	no unnecessary layers

👉 This is your anti-drift system

⸻

🧭 Step 4 — Lock the Trajectory

Choose direction:
	•	refine
	•	simplify
	•	clarify
	•	compress

Never choose: expand / add / stack

⸻

✨ Step 5 — Rebuild (Modern Version)

Now rebuild using:

Core + Constraints + Trajectory

⸻

⚠️ Step 6 — Add Failure Modes

Ground it so it doesn’t go off rails:
	•	what happens if overused?
	•	what misinterpretations occur?

⸻

🔁 Step 7 — Make it Transferable

Final test:
	•	can someone else use it without you?
	•	is it explainable in 1–2 sentences?

If not → simplify again

